## Product Bundles collection [/product-bundles]
Product bundles API allows you to list the information about the product bundle. Responses from this API will be retuned in JSON format only. Information about the constituent products that form a bundle will be side-loaded which will internally side load the product feature.  

### Product bundle
Product bundle as a resource represents following information:

| Property | Type | As request | As response |Description |
| :-------------------- | :---------- | :----------  | :---------- | ------------------------------------------------------------ |
| id | String | `Not applicable` | `Returned always` | Unique identifier for a bundle product. |
| description | String | `Not applicable` | `Returned always` | Bundle product description. |
| type | String | `Not applicable` | `Returned always` | Indicates the product type like `Services`. |
| excesses | Array of Integer | `Not applicable` | `Returned always` | Applicable levels of excess for the bundle. |
| paymentMethods | Array of PaymentMethods | `Not applicable` | `Returned always` | Applicable [payment methods](/api-reference/products.md#PaymentMethods) for the bundle. |
| products | Array of product | `Not applicable` | `Returned always` | [Product](/api-reference/products.md#product) information of all products which make a bundle. |

